==Arabic alphabet==

===Letter===
'''{{ARchar|ا / ـا}}'''

# Althought usually considered to be the first letter of the [[Arabic]] alphabet, the small [[hamza]] ({{ARchar|[[ء]]}}) that sit on top of {{ARchar|[[أ]]}} is really the first letter of the Arabic alphabet, and the tall column is its bearer. This article only deals with the lower part, the bearer, which is called {{ARchar|[[الف]]}} (’álif) and, without the hamza, is used to lengthen a preceding vowel, often [[a]]. It is followed by {{ARchar|[[ب]]}}.

===Pronunciation===
'''Combined with fathah:'''
{{ARchar|[[ـَا]]}} — ''''ā''''.

'''Combined with kasra:'''
{{ARchar|[[ـِا]]}} — ''''ī''''.

'''Combined with damma:'''
{{ARchar|[[ـُا]]}} — ''''ū''''.

